Privacy Policy for Battery Info PI
Last updated: February 26, 2025

This Privacy Policy explains how Battery Info PI ("we", "us", or "our") handles user information. 
By using the app, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

1. Data Collection & Usage
- Battery Info PI does not collect, store, or share any personal data.
- The app only reads battery-related information from the Android system API and displays it to the user in real-time.
- Information accessed includes battery percentage, charging status, voltage, current, temperature, battery health, estimated battery life, and power usage.
- No data is sent to external servers, third parties, or stored locally.

The app does not track, store, or transmit any user information.

2. Third-Party Services & Advertising
- Battery Info PI does not use third-party SDKs, analytics, or external APIs.
- The app does not display ads or serve any personalized content.
- No data is shared with advertisers or third-party services.

3. Security & Compliance
- Since no user data is collected or stored, no additional security measures are required.
- The app complies with Google Play’s Data Safety requirements.
- Battery Info PI does not target or collect data from children under 13.

4. Updates & Contact
This Privacy Policy may be updated if necessary. Any changes will be posted on the app’s store page and website.

For any questions or concerns, contact us at:
ilirhdev@gmail.com

Summary:
Battery Info PI does not collect, store, or share any user data. It only displays real-time battery information available through system APIs. 
No ads, no tracking, and no third-party involvement.